      "text": "Democracy has taken a number of forms, both in theory and practice. Some varieties of democracy provide better representation and more freedom for their citizens than others. However, if any democracy is not structured so as to prohibit the government from excluding the people from the legislative process, or any branch of government from altering the [[separation of powers]] in its own favour, then a branch of the system can accumulate too much power and destroy the democracy. - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democracy#Types_of_governmental_democracies wikipedia]"
